&lt;h2 id=&#34;using-flask-for-blazing-fast-rest-api-development:8f492df1de83072dcf6c4f4bd873bb9b&#34;&gt;Using Flask for blazing fast Rest API development&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;directory-structure:8f492df1de83072dcf6c4f4bd873bb9b&#34;&gt;Directory structure&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;.
|
├── utils
├── handlers
|   └──  todo.py
├── models
|   └──  todo.py
└── main.py
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;main.py - holds route and flask application initialization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;handlers - This directory holds handlers for different routes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;models - holds different data models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;quick-start:8f492df1de83072dcf6c4f4bd873bb9b&#34;&gt;Quick Start&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;python main.py&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;server will start on port 5000&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

